The "nickname" for the Yorkshire Terrier.  Yorkies are small dogs weighing betwee 3-7 pounds as adults.  The yorkie is a very playful, gentle breed.  Their main distinctive feature is the silk-like, steel blue hair that is often grown out for a long-hair breed.  Yorkies have expressive eyes and are very easy to train.  They require a great amout of maintanence, with frequent hair and teeth brushing sessions.  They do not eat a lot and have amaxing personailties.  Clearly the breed of choice.  It's been rumored that the Yorkies originated with the Bentley Benz and Gizmo Spike.